<item>
            <title>[HBASE-6474] Separate exception types for recoverable and non-recoverable errors </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6474</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While reading &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.quora.com/HBase/What-are-the-best-HBase-client-libraries-in-each-language?srid=hqw&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;about asynchbase&lt;/a&gt; I noticed that HBase turns exposes all errors to clients as IOEs rather than use the exception hierarchy to separate recoverable and non-recoverable exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12600680">HBASE-6474</key>
            <summary>Separate exception types for recoverable and non-recoverable errors </summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/improvement.png">Improvement</type>
