                            <comment id="13425264" author="lhofhansl" created="Mon, 30 Jul 2012 21:32:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are beginnings of this in the form of subclasses of IOException. For example unrecoverable actions throws back a subclass of DoNotRetryException to a client.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13426900" author="eli" created="Wed, 1 Aug 2012 21:13:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, would be good to doc that (eg in javadoc and/or explicit class names eg UnrecoverableException) and articulate the remaining work (perhaps as sub-tasks of this jira if it&apos;s a lot).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
